  "prompt": "What integer solutions to x and y are there for 167x+113y=1?",
  "response": "To find all integer solutions \\((x, y)\\) to the equation:\n\n\\[\n167x + 113y = 1\n\\]\n\nwe can use the **Extended Euclidean Algorithm**. Here's a step-by-step breakdown:\n\n### 1. Verify Solvability\nFirst, ensure that the equation has integer solutions by checking if the greatest common divisor (gcd) of 167 and 113 divides 1.\n\n- \\(167\\) and \\(113\\) are both prime numbers.\n- \\(\\gcd(167, 113) = 1\\)\n\nSince \\(1\\) divides \\(1\\), integer solutions exist.\n\n### 2. Apply the Extended Euclidean Algorithm\nWe seek integers \\(x\\) and \\(y\\) such that:\n\n\\[\n167x + 113y = 1\n\\]\n\n**Step-by-Step Computation:**\n\n1. **Divide 167 by 113:**\n   \\[\n   167 = 1 \\times 113 + 54 \\quad \\text{(Remainder = 54)}\n   \\]\n\n2. **Divide 113 by 54:**\n   \\[\n   113 = 2 \\times 54 + 5 \\quad \\text{(Remainder = 5)}\n   \\]\n\n3. **Divide 54 by 5:**\n   \\[\n   54 = 10 \\times 5 + 4 \\quad \\text{(Remainder = 4)}\n   \\]\n\n4. **Divide 5 by 4:**\n   \\[\n   5 = 1 \\times 4 + 1 \\quad \\text{(Remainder = 1)}\n   \\]\n\n5. **Express 1 as a combination of 5 and 4:**\n   \\[\n   1 = 5 - 1 \\times 4\n   \\]\n\n6. **Substitute back the value of 4:**\n   \\[\n   4 = 54 - 10 \\times 5 \\implies 1 = 5 - 1 \\times (54 - 10 \\times 5) = 11 \\times 5 - 1 \\times 54\n   \\]\n\n7. **Substitute back the value of 5:**\n   \\[\n   5 = 113 - 2 \\times 54 \\implies 1 = 11 \\times (113 - 2 \\times 54) - 1 \\times 54 = 11 \\times 113 - 23 \\times 54\n   \\]\n\n8. **Substitute back the value of 54:**\n   \\[\n   54 = 167 - 1 \\times 113 \\implies 1 = 11 \\times 113 - 23 \\times (167 - 1 \\times 113) = 34 \\times 113 - 23 \\times 167\n   \\]\n\n**Particular Solution:**\n\\[\nx = -23, \\quad y = 34\n\\]\n\n### 3. General Solution\nAll integer solutions can be expressed using a parameter \\(k\\) (where \\(k\\) is any integer):\n\n\\[\nx = -23 + 113k\n\\]\n\\[\ny = 34 - 167k\n\\]\n\n**Final Answer:**\n\nAll integer solutions are x = \u201323\u202f+\u202f113\u00b7k and y =\u00a034\u00a0\u2013\u00a0167\u00b7k for some integer k. Thus,\n\nx = \u221223 + 113k\ny = 34 \u2212 167k",
